title: Lamamra holds talks with German counterpart Annalena Baerbock
text: Minister of Foreign Affairs and National Community Abroad, Ramtane Lamamra, received on Monday, a phone call from his German counterpart, Annalena Baerbock.

During this telephone conversation, Baerbock expressed his country's condolences and solidarity with Algeria following the forest fires recorded in the northeastern provinces of the country and which caused several victims.
The telephone conversation was an opportunity to discuss the state of bilateral relations and prospects for strengthening them through the political will that drives the two countries' leaders.
